&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In Cornwall we are leading the development of new ways of working with our unscheduled and urgent care patients. To support this programme of change we are in a position to recruit Advanced Clinical Practitioners to lead the new service. They will be located on the Bodmin Community Hospital site in the heart of the county. These are Band 8A posts with a clear Advanced Practitioner role. These posts have clinical, educational, research and service development aspects. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to have previous experience in Advanced Practice in an emergency, minor injury and illness or unscheduled care setting, to include adults and paediatrics. The posts will be to provide clinical cover, predominantly day time hours, although the unit will operate 24 hours a day. There is a staffing development programme encompassing the Advanced Clinical Practitioner Apprenticeship at Masters level already in progress. You will demonstrate good communication skills, and a commitment to providing excellent care as part of the Urgent and minor injuries team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;THIS IS MY COMMUTE TO WORK. MAKE IT YOURS! (See attachment)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLaura InnissJob titleSister MIUEmail addresslaura.inniss@nhs.netTelephone number01208 251577&lt;/p&gt;
